cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper deals with the problem of pose estimation in outdoor scenes, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves training a neural network using unsupervised adversarial instance-level domain adaptation, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a pose estimation dataset (MS-COCO) and instance segmentation, which are common topics in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the problem of pedestrian detection is also addressed, which is a topic in robotics (cs.RO).
